chunk_content: Accreditation: Refers to accreditation by a national, regional, or internationally recognized accreditation body, such as College of American Pathologists (CAP), International Organization for Standardization (ISO) accreditation programs, regional accreditation bodies such as the South African National Accreditation System (SANAS), or other approved accreditation organizations. A laboratory- based testing site is assessed by a standardized set of criteria defined by an acceptable national, regional, or international organization. Accreditation certificates are a formal recognition that a laboratory is competent to perform clinical testing. Laboratory-based testing site accreditation status must be current. PT Participation: Defined as enrollment/participation in at least one round of a local, national, regional, and/or international external quality assurance or proficiency testing program at any time during the reporting period.
